  "texts": [
    "ScRNA-seq analysis reveals shared and genotype-specific alterations during early tumor development One of the advantages of cerebral organoids is that they contain heterogeneous neural cell populations and maintain differentiation hierarchies 20, thus can be used to study cellular heterogeneity and plasticity.",
    "To fully characterize the LEGOs on the single-cell level and to understand how different genetic mutations affect cellular heterogeneity, we performed scRNA-seq on 1-and 4month-old LEGOs.",
    "In total, we obtained results from 70617 cells for further analysis.",
    "We next performed UMAP (uniform manifold approximation and projection) analysis to visualize cell differentiation trajectory 21.",
    "UMAP of 1-month-old LEGOs show two major lineages (neuron and astrocyte), which was confirmed by the expression of immature neuronal marker DCX, astrocytic marker FABP7 and APOE (apolipoprotein E), and neural stem/progenitor marker SOX2 (Fig. 2a and Supplementary Fig."
  ]
}